[m
[1mNAME[0m[m
       grep, egrep, fgrep, rgrep - print lines that match patterns[m
[m
[1mSYNOPSIS[0m[m
       [1mgrep[0m [[4mOPTION[24m...] [4mPATTERNS[24m [[4mFILE[24m...][m
       [1mgrep[0m [[4mOPTION[24m...] [1m-e[0m [4mPATTERNS[24m ... [[4mFILE[24m...][m
       [1mgrep[0m [[4mOPTION[24m...] [1m-f[0m [4mPATTERN_FILE[24m ... [[4mFILE[24m...][m
[m
[1mDESCRIPTION[0m[m
       [1mgrep[0m  searches  for [4mPATTERNS[24m in each [4mFILE[24m.  [4mPATTERNS[24m is one or more patterns separated by newline[m
       characters, and [1mgrep[0m prints each line that matches  a  pattern.   Typically  [4mPATTERNS[24m  should  be[m
       quoted when [1mgrep[0m is used in a shell command.[m
[m
       A  [4mFILE[24m  of  “[1m-[0m”  stands for standard input.  If no [4mFILE[24m is given, recursive searches examine the[m
       working directory, and nonrecursive searches read standard input.[m
[m
       In addition, the variant programs [1megrep[0m, [1mfgrep[0m and [1mrgrep[0m are the same as  [1mgrep[0m [1m-E[0m,  [1mgrep[0m [1m-F[0m,  and[m
       [1mgrep[0m [1m-r[0m,   respectively.    These   variants  are  deprecated,  but  are  provided  for  backward[m
       compatibility.[m
[m
[1mOPTIONS[0m[m

[7m Manual page grep(1) line 48 (press h for help or q to quit)[27m[K[K [KESCESC[KOO[KBB[K              constituent character.  Similarly, it must be either at the end of the line or followed by[m

[7m Manual page grep(1) line 50 (press h for help or q to quit)[27m[K[K [KESCESC[KOO[KBB[K              the underscore.  This option has no effect if [1m-x[0m is also specified.[m

[?2004l[?1049h[22;0;0t[?1h=GREP(1)                                                                                      User Commands                                                                                     GREP(1)[m
[m
[1mNAME[0m[m
       grep, egrep, fgrep, rgrep - print lines that match patterns[m
[m
[1mSYNOPSIS[0m[m
       [1mgrep[0m [[4mOPTION[24m...] [4mPATTERNS[24m [[4mFILE[24m...][m
       [1mgrep[0m [[4mOPTION[24m...] [1m-e[0m [4mPATTERNS[24m ... [[4mFILE[24m...][m
       [1mgrep[0m [[4mOPTION[24m...] [1m-f[0m [4mPATTERN_FILE[24m ... [[4mFILE[24m...][m
[m
[1mDESCRIPTION[0m[m
       [1mgrep[0m  searches  for  [4mPATTERNS[24m  in each [4mFILE[24m.  [4mPATTERNS[24m is one or more patterns separated by newline characters, and [1mgrep[0m prints each line that matches a pattern.  Typically [4mPATTERNS[24m should be[m
       quoted when [1mgrep[0m is used in a shell command.[m
[m
       A [4mFILE[24m of “[1m-[0m” stands for standard input.  If no [4mFILE[24m is given, recursive searches examine the working directory, and nonrecursive searches read standard input.[m
[m
       In addition, the variant programs [1megrep[0m, [1mfgrep[0m and [1mrgrep[0m are the same as [1mgrep[0m [1m-E[0m, [1mgrep[0m [1m-F[0m,  and  [1mgrep[0m [1m-r[0m,  respectively.   These  variants  are  deprecated,  but  are  provided  for  backward[m
       compatibility.[m
[m
[1mOPTIONS[0m[m
   [1mGeneric[0m [1mProgram[0m [1mInformation[0m[m
       [1m--help[0m Output a usage message and exit.[m
[m
       [1m-V[0m, [1m--version[0m[m
              Output the version number of [1mgrep[0m and exit.[m
[m
   [1mPattern[0m [1mSyntax[0m[m
       [1m-E[0m, [1m--extended-regexp[0m[m
              Interpret [4mPATTERNS[24m as extended regular expressions (EREs, see below).[m
[m
       [1m-F[0m, [1m--fixed-strings[0m[m
              Interpret [4mPATTERNS[24m as fixed strings, not regular expressions.[m
[m
       [1m-G[0m, [1m--basic-regexp[0m[m
              Interpret [4mPATTERNS[24m as basic regular expressions (BREs, see below).  This is the default.[m
[m
       [1m-P[0m, [1m--perl-regexp[0m[m
              Interpret I<PATTERNS> as Perl-compatible regular expressions (PCREs).  This option is experimental when combined with the [1m-z[0m ([1m--null-data[0m) option, and [1mgrep[0m [1m-P[0m may warn of unimplemented[m
              features.[m
[m
   [1mMatching[0m [1mControl[0m[m
       [1m-e[0m [4mPATTERNS[24m, [1m--regexp=[0m[4mPATTERNS[24m[m
              Use [4mPATTERNS[24m as the patterns.  If this option is used multiple times or is combined with the [1m-f[0m ([1m--file[0m) option, search for all patterns given.  This option can be used  to  protect  a[m
              pattern beginning with “-”.[m
[m
       [1m-f[0m [4mFILE[24m, [1m--file=[0m[4mFILE[24m[m
              Obtain  patterns  from  [4mFILE[24m, one per line.  If this option is used multiple times or is combined with the [1m-e[0m ([1m--regexp[0m) option, search for all patterns given.  The empty file contains[m
              zero patterns, and therefore matches nothing.[m

[?2004h]0;xeldor@Ubuntu22: ~/Downloads/linux-exercises/chem[01;32mxeldor@Ubuntu22[00m:[01;34m~/Downloads/linux-exercises/chem[00m$ man grep
[?2004l[?1049h[22;0;0t[?1h=GREP(1)                                                                                      User Commands                                                                                     GREP(1)[m
[m
[1mNAME[0m[m
       grep, egrep, fgrep, rgrep - print lines that match patterns[m
[m
[1mSYNOPSIS[0m[m
       [1mgrep[0m [[4mOPTION[24m...] [4mPATTERNS[24m [[4mFILE[24m...][m
       [1mgrep[0m [[4mOPTION[24m...] [1m-e[0m [4mPATTERNS[24m ... [[4mFILE[24m...][m
       [1mgrep[0m [[4mOPTION[24m...] [1m-f[0m [4mPATTERN_FILE[24m ... [[4mFILE[24m...][m
[m
[1mDESCRIPTION[0m[m
       [1mgrep[0m  searches  for  [4mPATTERNS[24m  in each [4mFILE[24m.  [4mPATTERNS[24m is one or more patterns separated by newline characters, and [1mgrep[0m prints each line that matches a pattern.  Typically [4mPATTERNS[24m should be[m
       quoted when [1mgrep[0m is used in a shell command.[m
[m
       A [4mFILE[24m of “[1m-[0m” stands for standard input.  If no [4mFILE[24m is given, recursive searches examine the working directory, and nonrecursive searches read standard input.[m
[m
       In addition, the variant programs [1megrep[0m, [1mfgrep[0m and [1mrgrep[0m are the same as [1mgrep[0m [1m-E[0m, [1mgrep[0m [1m-F[0m,  and  [1mgrep[0m [1m-r[0m,  respectively.   These  variants  are  deprecated,  but  are  provided  for  backward[m
       compatibility.[m
[m
[1mOPTIONS[0m[m
   [1mGeneric[0m [1mProgram[0m [1mInformation[0m[m
       [1m--help[0m Output a usage message and exit.[m
[m
       [1m-V[0m, [1m--version[0m[m
              Output the version number of [1mgrep[0m and exit.[m
[m
   [1mPattern[0m [1mSyntax[0m[m
       [1m-E[0m, [1m--extended-regexp[0m[m
              Interpret [4mPATTERNS[24m as extended regular expressions (EREs, see below).[m
[m
       [1m-F[0m, [1m--fixed-strings[0m[m
